description.narrative:
The overarching goal of the EPAIU is to improve the quality and inclusiveness of environmental policy making and implementation in Ukraine by means of:
(a)    strengthening the influence of Ukrainian non-governmental environmental organizations on processes of designing, advocating, implementing and monitoring of environmental policies and practices at the national, regional and local levels;
(b)  based on the NGOs’ work, building a broad public awareness of, and demand for a problem-relevant, more inclusive, rights-based and conflict-sensitive approach to environmental policy and decision-making. 
The outcome objectives are:
(a)    to strengthen the environmental movement by means of fostering institutional development, policy, advocacy and communication  capacities of a new cohort of environmental NGOs and think tanks;
(b)  to improve public policy debate on the environmental protection as a cross-cutting issue of economic development and implementation of the Association Agreement between Ukraine and the EU;
(c)   to contribute to raising public awareness of the environment as a value and public good;
(d)   to develop and expand networks of public and private-sector stakeholders that collaborate on mainstreaming environmental protection.
The immediate objective (purpose) of EPAIU is to support the creation and development of a cohort of institutionally capable, transparently governed, accountable and publicly recognized environmental organizations that will engage in environmental policy-making, implementation and monitoring and build a broad and inclusive constituency. Through ongoing work and influence of these NGOs the programme strives to achieve a new quality of national and regional / local environmental policy and to grow  informed public demand for policies and practices that ensure the environmental background.
Output objectives:
(a) Selection, through a competitive procedure and a nation-wide call, a cohort of 10-15 new environmental NGOs to take part in the Environmental Policy and Advocacy Initiative for Ukraine (EPAIU);
(b) Design and implement comprehensive governance, organizational management, strategic planning, policy research, advocacy, and communication capacity development program;
(c) Roll out institutional grant program to a circle of the selected and trained environmental NGOs and think tanks;
(d) Create an efficient network of NGOs working in the field of development and implementation of national and regional / local environmental policies;
(e) Create infrastructure for policy dialogues between environmental organizations, governmental agencies and socially responsible businesses.
